
                             FLAGLET CODE 
		     http://www.flaglets.org
              Fast and exact wavelet transform on the ball
  ----------------------------------------------------------------

DESCRIPTION
     The FLAGLET code provides functionality to perform fast and exact
     wavelet transform on the ball.

VERSION
     Release 2.0b1, November 2015

AUTHORS
     B. Leistedt (www.ixkael.com/blog)
     J. D. McEwen (www.jasonmcewen.org)

REFERENCES
     B. Leistedt, J. D. McEwen, T. Kitching, H. V. Peiris, 3D weak lensing with spin wavelets on the ball.

     B. Leistedt and J. D. McEwen, Exact wavelets on the ball, IEEE Trans. Sig. Proc., 60, 2012.

     J. D. McEwen, M. Büttner, B. Leistedt, H. V. Peiris, Y. Wiaux, P. Vandergheynst, Spin scale-discretised wavelets on the sphere, IEEE TSP, 2015.

     J. D. McEwen, M. Büttner, B. Leistedt, H. V. Peiris, Y. Wiaux, A novel sampling theorem on the rotation group, IEEE TSP, 2015.

     B. Leistedt, J. D. McEwen, P. Vandergheynst and Y. Wiaux, S2LET: A code to perform fast wavelet analysis on the sphere, Astronomy & Astrophysics, submitted, 2012.

DOCUMENTATION
     See doc/index.html

INSTALLATION
     See documentation

REQUIREMENTS
     FLAG (http://astro-informatics.github.io/flag)
     S2LET (http://www.s2let.org)
     SO3 (http://www.sothree.org)
     SSHT (http://www.spinsht.org)
     FFTW (http://www.fftw.org)

DOWNLOAD
     http://www.flaglets.org

SUPPORT
     Please email the authors.

NOTE
     The package is in beta and is still under development.
     Please report problems/bugs by email to: boris.leistedt@gmail.com

